The paper deals with the problem of space division multiple access (SDMA) in wireless networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of beamforming techniques (cs.MM) and the impact of interference (cs.SI) on network performance. Additionally, the paper considers a decentralized (ad hoc) network architecture (cs.CE).
